{"author":{"id":"729f4229091d502775e0e5c4bfc138609955b348584d955f4229a3d76892d2a9"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1448649165,"nonce":"KQqmWXnSxEagw4qyhS64yjYhiSQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2MDE4NjUyMw==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/417#issuecomment-160186523"},"message":"@erasche: pkg-config is doing the correct thing. Compilers like gcc/clang/etc. look through directories specified by `-I` options first, followed by those set in `C*_INCLUDE_PATH` and finally the default system directories (e.g., `/usr/include`) when looking for headers. Since disks aren't always fast and many programs will require compiling a large number of files, it's best if the compiler doesn't need to look through the same directory twice. My understanding is that that's why `pkg-config` is behaving in this manner.\n\nSince this is completely the fault of matplotlib, I'll post a bug report there. That won't resolve the immediate problem but will at least prevent this in the future :)","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1448659561,"nonce":"7Yr+Avncu+kKr7dkg+EBtv2Inbc=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2MDIwNjIyOA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/417#issuecomment-160206228"},"message":"Looks like this will get fixed in matplotlib 1.5.1 due to https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib/pull/5578.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1450793168,"nonce":"JD8pz6eIsjp/Yqu7yfGi/E+CjXM=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2NjYyNTIyNQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/417#issuecomment-166625225"},"message":"This is fixed now, I'll close it.","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1450793168,"nonce":"DffsaXFIVa/6Q1kVHUmtgUfE31Y=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50NDk4NTI0NjE5"},"status":2}]}